{
  "slug": "imessage",
  "name": "Imessage",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "iMessage channel for Claude Code — reads chat.db directly, sends via AppleScript. Built-in access control; manage pairing, allowlists, and policy via /imessage:access.",
  "longDescription": "Ships **1 MCP server** and **2 skills** (`/imessage:configure`, `/imessage:access`). Reads `chat.db` directly via SQLite and sends messages through AppleScript — no external server or background process. Provides **2 tools**: `reply` (text + file attachments with automatic chunking) and `chat_messages` (threaded conversation history for DMs and groups). Polls for new messages every second using a watermark system to prevent replays. macOS only — requires Full Disk Access for your terminal. Cannot send tapbacks, edit messages, or create threads.",
  "compatibility": [
    "claude"
  ],
